1
00:01:11,671 --> 00:01:14,774
(lighthearted music)

2
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:18,444
(puking)

3
00:01:18,445 --> 00:01:19,679
- Are you okay?

4
00:01:22,048 --> 00:01:23,315
Here.

5
00:01:23,316 --> 00:01:25,617
(coughing)

6
00:01:25,618 --> 00:01:28,688
(lighthearted music)

7
00:01:37,330 --> 00:01:39,465
Let me get some water for you.

8
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:41,266
- Thank you.

9
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:44,937
- Here, this will make you feel better.

10
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,472
- [Woman] Christopher is a man

11
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:49,441
who's aware of his surroundings.

12
00:01:49,442 --> 00:01:50,976
- Thank you.
- Are you okay?

13
00:01:50,977 --> 00:01:52,377
- Yeah.

14
00:01:52,378 --> 00:01:54,780
- [Woman] Fate tore them apart.

15
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:57,283
Destiny brought them together.

16
00:01:58,151 --> 00:02:01,254
(lighthearted music)

17
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:13,819
- No!

18
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,826
(dramatic music)

19
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:36,275
(knocking)

20
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:37,443
- Christopher?

21
00:04:38,911 --> 00:04:40,512
Do you ever answer your phone?

22
00:04:40,513 --> 00:04:42,081
- I don't want to talk to him.

23
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,450
- You look like hell.

24
00:04:45,485 --> 00:04:46,452
Why aren't you ready?

25
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:47,653
- I'm not going into work today,

26
00:04:47,654 --> 00:04:48,755
I'm not feeling well.

27
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:52,057
- Yeah, this is probably
why you're not feeling well,

28
00:04:52,058 --> 00:04:52,959
you drink too much.

29
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:55,561
- Look, I only had a couple, all right?

30
00:04:56,696 --> 00:04:58,630
- We missed you last night.

31
00:04:58,631 --> 00:04:59,631
- Sorry.

32
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:04,536
- You've been late with your columns.

33
00:05:04,537 --> 00:05:06,772
If you don't watch it,
you're gonna get fired.

34
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:07,839
I mean, I understand that, you know,

35
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,907
Savannah died six months-

36
00:05:08,908 --> 00:05:10,075
- Will you shut up, please?

37
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:11,076
Just...

38
00:05:12,245 --> 00:05:13,245
Just...

39
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:16,448
- Sorry.

40
00:05:19,952 --> 00:05:22,321
- Is six months enough for you?

41
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:24,824
I spent 22 years with her, 22!

42
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:27,993
I miss her.

43
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,228
I loved her so much.

44
00:05:32,098 --> 00:05:33,098
- I didn't mean...

45
00:05:33,866 --> 00:05:36,235
I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to make matters worse.

46
00:05:38,771 --> 00:05:41,907
Listen, but I was reading
your last article,

47
00:05:41,908 --> 00:05:42,975
"The Singing Forest".

48
00:05:45,144 --> 00:05:46,144
Very interesting.

49
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:52,452
About how searching for your soul and...

50
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,120
Do you really think people can connect

51
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:56,455
with their past lives?

52
00:05:56,456 --> 00:05:58,490
- Yeah, some people can.

53
00:05:58,491 --> 00:06:01,193
The psychic I interviewed
for this column last month

54
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,096
told me things not even Savannah knew.

55
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,997
And she donates her time to the police

56
00:06:05,998 --> 00:06:07,433
to help solve crimes.

57
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:10,001
She helped me.

58
00:06:10,002 --> 00:06:13,472
She took me back, to a
Nazi concentration camp

59
00:06:13,473 --> 00:06:15,707
in the middle of the forest.

60
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,943
It's funny, because as she was talking,

61
00:06:17,944 --> 00:06:19,711
I can see everything
she was talking about,

62
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:20,980
it was so clear.

63
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,884
But who's to know what's real.

64
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:29,255
(dramatic music)

65
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,146
- What were you doing in the camp?

66
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:56,849
- It's a little confusing, but,

67
00:06:57,884 --> 00:07:02,621
she said I was helping
to hide and feed the Jews

68
00:07:02,622 --> 00:07:05,457
who were being persecuted by the Nazis.

69
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:08,360
I was part of a Jewish
underground resistance group,

70
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:09,661
the Chug Chaluzi.

71
00:07:09,662 --> 00:07:12,130
And we hid and fed Jews in the churches

72
00:07:12,131 --> 00:07:14,734
to keep them from being
sent to concentration camps.

73
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:20,473
She kept referring to me as "Jo".

74
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:24,876
- As in Joe and John?

75
00:07:24,877 --> 00:07:26,879
- No, as in J-O, Jo.

76
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:32,617
Anyway, after I became
the head of the resistance

77
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:36,021
I was captured when
another group was betrayed

78
00:07:36,022 --> 00:07:38,757
shortly before the
Russians liberated Berlin.

79
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:39,992
I was tortured and hung.

80
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,194
- She told you this?

81
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:43,462
- Yeah.

82
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,629
- And you believed her?

83
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,164
- After telling me things only I know,

84
00:07:46,165 --> 00:07:47,767
you're damn right I believe her.

85
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:55,641
Listen, tell the boss I'll be
going out of town for a while.

86
00:07:56,542 --> 00:07:57,609
- Where out of town?

87
00:07:57,610 --> 00:08:01,113
- Just out, to see my daughter, Destiny.

88
00:08:03,382 --> 00:08:04,382
- I never knew you had a daughter,

89
00:08:04,383 --> 00:08:06,284
and I've known you for many years.

90
00:08:06,285 --> 00:08:08,187
- I'm a private person, you know that.

91
00:08:09,522 --> 00:08:11,123
She's getting married next week.

92
00:08:12,191 --> 00:08:13,525
- You never told me
anything about a daughter.

93
00:08:13,526 --> 00:08:14,594
- Nevermind that!

94
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,529
Look, she turns 22 next week,

95
00:08:17,530 --> 00:08:19,298
and she's getting married on her birthday.

96
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,269
- Look, Chris, I'm very
happy for you, I mean...

97
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,437
And you should be happy for her,

98
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:27,072
that's why you need to sober up,

99
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:28,406
you need to clean yourself up.

100
00:08:28,407 --> 00:08:29,407
I mean...

101
00:08:31,944 --> 00:08:32,778
I gotta go.

102
00:08:32,779 --> 00:08:35,046
I've gotta turn in some
artwork to a client.

103
00:08:35,047 --> 00:08:36,749
- Okay, I'll call you later.

104
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:39,351
- Keep your chin up.

105
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:40,419
- Yeah, thanks.

106
00:08:50,096 --> 00:08:52,264
(thunder rumbles)

107
00:08:52,265 --> 00:08:53,566
- Hi, honey, we're home!

108
00:08:57,570 --> 00:08:58,504
- Hey.

109
00:08:58,505 --> 00:09:00,171
You finally made it.

110
00:09:00,172 --> 00:09:02,008
Come on in, I got stuff on the stove.

111
00:09:06,178 --> 00:09:08,113
- God, he looks so familiar.

112
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:09,582
- Let me help you with that.

113
00:09:10,483 --> 00:09:11,384
- I know we usually eat out,

114
00:09:11,385 --> 00:09:14,319
but this is a special occasion, right?

115
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,320
- Yeah.

116
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:18,857
- [Ben] Excuse me, sir,
can you hand me that plate?

117
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:20,359
- Please, call me Christopher.

118
00:09:22,695 --> 00:09:23,695
- Christopher.

119
00:09:24,463 --> 00:09:25,530
You okay?

120
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:26,698
- Yeah.

121
00:09:26,699 --> 00:09:29,834
I'm just glad Destiny's
done so well for herself.

122
00:09:29,835 --> 00:09:31,269
- [Destiny] Thanks, Dad.

123
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,238
- Make yourself comfortable.

124
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:33,538
Dinner's almost ready.

125
00:09:33,539 --> 00:09:34,373
- Yeah, sure.

126
00:09:34,373 --> 00:09:35,308
- Oh, come with me.

127
00:09:35,309 --> 00:09:37,810
It is time for the tour guide.

128
00:09:43,182 --> 00:09:45,183
- How about a little champagne

129
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:47,320
to celebrate your arrival?

130
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:52,391
- [Christopher] Thank you.

131
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,660
- Oh, I forgot the salt.

132
00:09:55,661 --> 00:09:56,529
- Oh, don't worry.

133
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:57,529
I'll get it.

134
00:09:59,532 --> 00:10:00,533
- So, mister...

135
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,467
Christopher.

136
00:10:02,468 --> 00:10:03,402
How was your trip?

137
00:10:03,403 --> 00:10:04,470
- Pleasant, thank you.

138
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,472
So, how long have you known my Destiny?

139
00:10:07,473 --> 00:10:11,209
- Um, seems like we've known
each other all our lives.

140
00:10:11,210 --> 00:10:13,012
We've been together about three years now.

141
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:15,615
- Destiny tells me you're a model.

142
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:18,183
- As in a citizen?

143
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:19,018
I don't think so.

144
00:10:19,019 --> 00:10:21,019
I'm a good example not to follow.

145
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,321
- You're perfect, sweetie.

146
00:10:25,725 --> 00:10:27,226
Everything looks so wonderful.

147
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:29,362
- Thank you.

148
00:10:29,363 --> 00:10:30,729
- You're a good cook.

149
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:31,763
- Thanks.

150
00:10:31,764 --> 00:10:33,699
- So, honey, how was your photo shoot?

151
00:10:34,734 --> 00:10:36,101
- I've been meaning to
talk to you about that.

152
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:39,037
It was good, and some of the guys

153
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:40,773
want to take me out tomorrow night.

154
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:42,641
- Mm.

155
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:45,544
I forgot, the bachelor party.

156
00:10:47,713 --> 00:10:50,516
- [Ben] But if you want,
we can hang out tomorrow.

157
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:53,052
- Yeah, sure, I like that idea.

158
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:55,454
- Hm, how about a toast?

159
00:10:57,523 --> 00:10:59,190
To family.

160
00:10:59,191 --> 00:11:00,725
- What no one shall separate.

161
00:11:00,726 --> 00:11:01,560
- [Christopher] Cheers.

162
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,560
- Cheers.

163
00:11:03,295 --> 00:11:06,532
(dramatic piano music)

164
00:11:42,435 --> 00:11:44,335
Good show, don't you think?

165
00:11:44,336 --> 00:11:45,504
- Interesting.

166
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:49,908
- She always does this,
I've seen this film already.

167
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:52,510
But don't worry, I won't
ruin the ending for you,

168
00:11:52,511 --> 00:11:54,379
it's best if you figure
it out for yourself.

169
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,681
- She's always slept like this in my lap,

170
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,350
ever since she was a little baby.

171
00:12:05,091 --> 00:12:06,225
- I'm glad you're here.

172
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,795
- I'm happy to be here.

173
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,737
- See you tomorrow, bright and early.

174
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:22,041
- Bright and early it is.

175
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:27,011
- Dad?

176
00:12:27,012 --> 00:12:28,012
- Hm?

177
00:12:28,013 --> 00:12:30,081
- I've gotta go to work now.

178
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:30,916
Okay, there's coffee on the stove,

179
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:32,283
and bagels and fruit in the fridge,

180
00:12:32,284 --> 00:12:34,319
so you help yourself to
anything you want, okay?

181
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,223
- [Christopher] Thanks, sweetheart.

182
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:42,762
- I'm so happy you're here.

183
00:12:44,997 --> 00:12:46,464
Okay, I left my work number on the fridge,

184
00:12:46,465 --> 00:12:48,399
so you call me if you need anything, okay?

185
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,335
- I'm sure I'll be fine.

186
00:12:50,336 --> 00:12:51,936
- Okay.

187
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:54,273
I'm gonna be home late
from work again tonight.

188
00:12:55,407 --> 00:12:58,376
Ben's getting ready to
take you around, though.

189
00:12:58,377 --> 00:13:00,111
You guys have fun, okay?

190
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:01,613
- Yeah, we will.

191
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:02,981
- Okay.

192
00:13:02,982 --> 00:13:03,982
Bye.

193
00:13:06,318 --> 00:13:08,753
(waves crashing)

194
00:13:08,754 --> 00:13:11,857
(lighthearted music)

195
00:13:20,499 --> 00:13:21,567
- I love coming here.

196
00:13:22,601 --> 00:13:23,601
It's very relaxing.

197
00:13:24,403 --> 00:13:25,570
And every time I feel down,

198
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:27,973
or I just want to clear
my mind, I come here.

199
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:30,142
- I know how you feel.

200
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,111
Nature has a way of putting us here

201
00:13:33,112 --> 00:13:34,814
and sometimes forgetting about us.

202
00:13:36,782 --> 00:13:37,782
Ben...

203
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,920
Do you believe in reincarnation?

204
00:13:41,921 --> 00:13:44,289
(waves crashing)

205
00:13:44,290 --> 00:13:47,125
- You mean like dying and coming back?

206
00:13:47,126 --> 00:13:48,694
- Yeah, something like that.

207
00:13:50,596 --> 00:13:51,796
- I don't know, I never
really thought about it.

208
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:53,198
Why?

209
00:13:53,199 --> 00:13:55,267
- 'Cause you remind me of someone that...

210
00:13:58,337 --> 00:13:59,971
- That what?

211
00:13:59,972 --> 00:14:01,072
- Nevermind.

212
00:14:01,073 --> 00:14:01,907
- No, what?

213
00:14:01,908 --> 00:14:03,508
- No, it would sound nutty, it's-

214
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:04,876
- No, go ahead, tell me.

215
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:05,877
I'm all ears.

216
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:08,513
- Okay.

217
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:11,950
Have you ever had an experience

218
00:14:11,951 --> 00:14:13,718
where you feel like you've met someone

219
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:16,087
at another time or another place,

220
00:14:16,088 --> 00:14:18,923
and then all of a sudden
you see that same person

221
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:20,159
in a different place?

222
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,862
- No. (laughs)

223
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,064
Hey, that's kinda weird.

224
00:14:26,131 --> 00:14:27,733
- I told you it would sound nutty.

225
00:14:29,068 --> 00:14:31,336
(waves crashing)

226
00:14:31,337 --> 00:14:34,372
- Yeah, you know, I think
there's that TV show, "Sights".

227
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:36,007
Yeah, they had this
one story about a ghost

228
00:14:36,008 --> 00:14:37,542
who took possession of
one of the family members

229
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:39,010
who lived in this house.

230
00:14:39,011 --> 00:14:41,479
I mean, in no time at all, an uncle,

231
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,214
or I think it was a cousin,

232
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:46,184
he was running around acting like a ghost.

233
00:14:46,185 --> 00:14:48,052
I mean, they have pictures
of it and everything,

234
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:49,053
it was freaky.

235
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:52,457
Christopher.

236
00:14:53,292 --> 00:14:54,260
Hello? (claps)

237
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:55,094
Christopher?

238
00:14:55,094 --> 00:14:55,928
- Yeah.

239
00:14:55,929 --> 00:14:58,096
- Are you all right?

240
00:14:58,097 --> 00:14:59,464
You kinda spaced out for a minute there.

241
00:14:59,465 --> 00:15:01,165
- Yeah, I was thinking.

242
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:02,901
- Oh, great.

243
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:06,037
- I was thinking of
how miraculous life is.

244
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:07,071
You know, it's the little things

245
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,541
that make me stop and
wonder about our existence.

246
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:14,412
You know, like, even though
science is improved now,

247
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,848
you have to stop and
wonder how every object

248
00:15:16,849 --> 00:15:18,950
like an airplane can fly through thin air,

249
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:23,956
or an ocean liner can float on
something as light as water.

250
00:15:24,023 --> 00:15:26,090
Isn't that incredible
how nature prepares us

251
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:28,027
to deal with our own...

252
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:34,799
It's like our souls are driving
vehicles of flesh and blood.

253
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:37,569
You know, we cut ourselves, we bleed,

254
00:15:38,904 --> 00:15:41,940
and our bodies would heal
the wound or the sickness,

255
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,808
or sometimes they...

256
00:15:43,809 --> 00:15:47,178
(drowned out speaking)

257
00:15:47,179 --> 00:15:49,747
- I try not to think too
much about that stuff.

258
00:15:49,748 --> 00:15:50,582
All right?

259
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:51,883
Life is too short as it is,

260
00:15:51,884 --> 00:15:53,685
I don't think we have
enough days on the planet

261
00:15:53,686 --> 00:15:56,955
to even begin to figure all that out.

262
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,691
- There's got to be a
higher power at work.

263
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:02,695
When my wife died, I didn't want to live.

264
00:16:03,996 --> 00:16:05,097
I felt empty.

265
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:10,134
There was a time I allowed
myself to waste away.

266
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:12,670
I just sat in my house and did nothing

267
00:16:12,671 --> 00:16:16,441
until one morning I woke up and felt like

268
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:18,242
I needed to continue living,

269
00:16:18,243 --> 00:16:20,979
not for my sake, but for
those who care about me,

270
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,314
those who need me.

271
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:27,085
